{
  "id": "palouse",
  "title": "Palouse",
  "type": "photography",
  "parent": "Photography",
  "narrative": "Palouse is a photographic study of the farmed landscape of the Palouse region of the inland Pacific Northwest, where wind-deposited loess has built a terrain of deep, rolling hills given almost entirely to dryland agriculture. The work reads the cultivated surface as a record of both elemental force and human labor — contour-plowed slopes, seasonal color, and the long geometry of wheat, barley, and legume fields shaped to the undulation of the land.",
  "year": "2013",
  "location": "Palouse region, southeastern Washington and northern Idaho, USA",
  "medium": "Photography",
  "process": "Photographic survey of the cultivated Palouse landscape, made with a Nikon D800.",
  "edition": "of 3, 2 APs",
  "cta": "Inquire",
  "visualDescription": "Smooth, rolling hills of farmland fill the lower frame beneath a wide, pale, nearly empty sky. The land moves in soft waves — bands of vivid green young crops and darker tilled earth follow the contours of the hills in fine parallel rows, like brushstrokes tracing the land's undulation. The compositions are spare and near-abstract: a quiet, sculpted horizon of cultivated earth meeting luminous sky, with large areas of open space. Color shifts with the season from bright spring green toward summer gold and bare brown soil.",
  "descriptionSections": {
    "scientific": "shot circa 2013 (artist recollection); Nikon D800; Palouse region; rolling loess hills up to ~500 ft over Columbia River Basalt; wind-deposited Pleistocene glacial silt; one of the most productive non-irrigated (dryland) farming regions in the world; largest U.S. lentil-growing region",
    "visual": "rolling, contoured, striped, cultivated, seasonal, green-to-gold, sculpted, undulating, patterned",
    "geographic": "Palouse region; southeastern Washington; northern Idaho; south of Spokane to the Snake River; Whitman County; Latah County",
    "atmospheric": "open, pastoral, expansive, weathered, quiet, seasonal, sunlit",
    "spatial": "rolling loess hills, contour-plowed slopes, field geometry, layered ridgelines, broad agricultural distance"
  },
